== Documentaries ==
In 2006, Annette von Wangenheim directed the documentary ''Joséphine Baker: Black Diva in a White Mans World'', about Baker's life and work from a perspective that analyses images of Black people in popular culture.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Josephine Baker: Black Diva in a White Man's World {{!}} San Francisco Film Festival |url=http://history.sffs.org/films/film_details.php?id=5850&searchfield= |access-date=2024-03-19 |website=history.sffs.org}}</ref>

In 2007, Mark Miller published his biography of [[Valaida Snow]]: ''High Hat, Trumpet and Rhythm'' (Toronto, Mercury Press), in which he evokes Valaida's partnership and rivalry with J.Baker: p.&nbsp;8, 38, 44–45, 52, 57, 61, 94, 107, 120–121.

In 2018, ''Josephine Baker: The Story of an Awakening'', directed by Ilana Navaro,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Joséphine Baker, the story of an awakening |url=https://kepler22productions.com/films/josephine-baker-premiere-icone-noire/?lang=en |access-date=2024-03-19 |website=Kepler22 Productions |language=en-US}}</ref> premiered at the Beirut Art Film Festival in 2018.

